House Democrats prepared to mount a quick challenge this week to
the House Republican leadership in an effort to force campaign
finance legislation to a vote. At the same time, Republicans were
quietly considering whether to drop their traditional opposition to
another Democratic issues _ a minimum wage increase. By Alison
Mitchell.
