<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CPT-SPORTSNET-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLENTY OF CHOICES ONLINE FOR NFL DRAFTNIKS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOMMY CUMMINGS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   It's time to break out NFL draft expert Mel Kiper's Draft Kit.
You know, the one available for $24.95 through Melkiper.com.
</P>
<P>
   For those who dabble with mock drafts don't have to panic if
they haven't ordered their kit. Mel Kiper's Draft Kit, assembled by
ESPN's draft guru, is only one of many online resources for this
weekend's draft.
</P>
<P>
   The big-media sites, such as ESPN.com, CBS SportsLine,
MSNBCSPORTS.com and ``The Sporting News,'' are standard with
scouting reports, analysis, draft diaries, player profiles,
contests, draft history and mock drafts. A few of the more
interesting sites are the homemade pages network resources such as
draft guides and general information in one handy index.
</P>
<P>
   For Jimmy Johnson-wannabes, here are a few recommendations:
</P>
<P>
   DRAFT CENTRAL (nfldraft.espn.go.com): In this case, the official
word is the best word. ESPN.com and NFL.com have pooled their
resources for draft analysis and coverage that should satiate even
the most avid draftnik.
</P>
<P>
   The site's best feature is its DraftTracker, which is designed
to allow draft junkies to analyze selections in real time and sort
selections by player, position, NFL or college team.
</P>
<P>
   Draft Central's content is constantly updated around the clock
and exclusive features are added each day leading up to the draft.
A live mock draft is scheduled for today. Draft Central also plans
to go live on draft weekend with audio feeds from ESPN Radio and
player news conferences, chats with top picks and analysis from Gil
Brandt, former Cowboys director of player personnel.
</P>
<P>
   THE WAR ROOM (www.nflwarroom.com): Former NFL scout Gary Horton
brings his publication online and shares some of his subscription
site's content through ``The Sporting News'' Online
(www.sportingnews.com). Endorsed by Jimmy Johnson, The War Room
offers detailed analysis and exclusive content.
</P>
<P>
   MIGUEL'S COLLECTION OF 1999 NFL DRAFT LINKS
(w3.nai.net/(tilde)nepats/mydraftlinks.html): The name and address
might be cumbersome, but the research done by Miguel Benzan, a New
England Patriots fan from Hartford, Ct., is tough to match.
</P>
<P>
   Benzan has the standard links, but what sets his site apart is
his detailed review of each link's highlights. He rates the sites
that have general information, mock drafts, draft guides and mock
draft contests.
</P>
<P>
   BS SHEET (members.aol.com/bssheet): James Brylinski of Orchard
Park, N.Y., has put together an impressive collection of links to
hundreds of NFL and college football articles from newspaper sites.
Brylinski updates his commercial-free 4-year-old site daily and
provides detailed draft prospect information.
</P>
<P>
   MARTY AND MATT MATARAZZO'S DRAFT INFO PAGE
(members.tripod.com/prodraft): This father-and-son effort
specializes in the sleepers at each position.
</P>
<P>
   THE DRAFT GURU (www.draftguru.com): This site bills itself as
the only draft analysis and fantasy ranking service that is updated
year-round. It includes position rankings, sleepers listings, top
250 rankings and top prospect biographies.
</P>
<P>
   THE WINNING DRIVE'S 1999 MOCK DRAFT (thewinningdrive.com: This
tipsheet site played host to a mock draft with guests from several
football-related sites analyzing their selections.
</P>
<P>
   THE DRAFT DODGER (www.draftdodger.com): This is a must-see site
for Philadelphia Eagles fans. The Draft Dodger has a full
seven-round mock draft that includes the compensatory selections.
</P>
<P>
   MARK'S DALLAS COWBOYS 1999 NFL DRAFT SPECIAL
(home.sprintmail.com/(tilde)magodfrey/FSP-cdraft.htm): This site
addresses the Cowboys' needs and strategies and features a
seven-round mock draft for the team.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, after sorting through these sites, the last thing
you'll need is a Mel Kiper draft kit.
</P>
<P>
   (Tommy Cummings writes about the Internet for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can contact him at (817) 390-7397. E-mail:
dragon(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
