<P>
   FAMOUS-CITIES _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Paris is the city of
lights. New York is the city that never sleeps. San Francisco is
the city by the bay. Chicago has the Sears Tower, St. Louis has its
arch. But what if you're a sleepy, one-stoplight town that's
archless and far from world-reknown? What if you're ... Okeechobee,
Fla.? Well, you anoint yourself the Speckled Perch Capital of the
World and wear the title with pride. And you have an annual
speckled perch festival that attracts about 12,000 people a year.
The titles are adopted locally and usually related to a major local
agricultural staple, manufacturing product or natural resource.
There is no officially sanctioned body that deals out official
Capital of the World status, but some towns and counties get
serious by trademarking their titles to prevent others from
poaching. Several ``world-famous'' cities and their claims to fame
are included. (Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
