   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT &LR;  (``e'' code)
</P>
<P>
   MET-TICKET (New York) _ Ever so quietly, the Metropolitan Museum
of Art has raised its suggested admission price to $10, from $8.
The price jump, which went into effect on Mar. 1, is necessary to
shore up the museum's finances, Met officials say. By Judith
Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   COLLECTOR (Undated) _ Before he died suddenly last year at 81 of
a heart attack, David Feigenbaum led the secret life of a collector
of Citizen Kane-like obsessiveness. He filled almost every inch of
his two-story house in Marblehead, Mass., with things, including
books, guns, model boats, Civil War and World War II paraphernalia
and an old Scottish Bible collection. And in the basement, amid
jewels, old manuscripts and historic letters, was an extraordinary
cache of mid-19th-century daguerreotypes. By Margaret Loke.
</P>
<P>
   TRUE-HEMINGWAY (Boston) _ Authors, scholars and fans gathered
here for the Hemingway Centennial conference at the Kennedy Library
and debated the wisdom and taste of producing a work like ``True at
First Light'' _ the posthumous Ernest Hemingway novel about an
African safari, edited by his son Patrick from a longer manuscript.
The book is to be published by Scribners this summer and is
expected to be the last of his leftover works to see the light of
day. By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   HONGKONG-JEWS (Hong Kong) _ Arts Abroad: The French photographer
Fred Brenner continues his documentation of the Jewish Diaspora, in
this case the Jewish community in Hong Kong. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   TV-NOTES (Undated) _ News and notes on television. By Bill
Carter and Lawrie Mifflin.
</P>
<P>
   FASCIST-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Fascist Revolution,'' by
George Mosse (Howard Fertig, Inc). Reviewed by Richard Bernstein.
</P>
<P>
   TV-OLD-MOVIES (Undated) _ A critic's notebook on old movies on
television. By Walter Goodman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;  (``s'' code)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ARATON-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on the
Knicks, who play the 76ers tonight. By Harvey Araton.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-SIXERS (New York) _ Philadelphia at the Knicks, 7:35
p.m. ET start. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NETS-CLIPPERS (Los Angeles) _ N.J. Nets at the L.A.
Clippers, 10:30 p.m. ET start. By Chris Broussard.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-ORIOLES (New York) _ Baltimore at the Yankees, 7:35
p.m. ET start. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-DRAFT (New York) _ Advancing Saturday's NFL draft. By
Thomas George.
</P>
