<HEADLINE>
`STAR WARS': THEN AND NOW 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Force is with George Lucas as he prepares to bring ``The
Phantom Menace'' to the screen on May 19. A quick look at the
numbers reveals that he's in a galaxy far, far away from the one
that launched ``Star Wars'' in 1977.
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars'' box-office total for its initial run: $400
million-plus.
</P>
<P>
   Amount ``Phantom'' is expected to gross: $1.2 billion-plus.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Estimated cost to make ``Star Wars'': $10 million
</P>
<P>
   Estimated cost to make ``Phantom'': $100 million-plus
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Number of ``Star Wars'' action figures on shelves in May 1977: 0 &QL; 
Number of ``Phantom'' action figures on shelves in May 1999:
millions, along with dozens of other products including ``Micro
Machine'' vehicles and collectibles
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Cost of a Han Solo action figure in 1978: less than $15
</P>
<P>
   Cost of the same action figure in mint condition in 1999: $550
</P>
<P>
   Cost is impossible to pinpoint, as Lucasfilm is private and owns
its own premiere effects house, Industrial Light &AMP; Magic. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   According to Tomart's Price Guide to Worldwide Star Wars
Collectibles, Second Edition.
</P>
</TEXT>
