   MINDSPRING _ ATLANTA _ Charles Brewer testifies before Senate
telecomm and commerce subcommitte. What he said and hopefully,
interview with Brewer. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ST-JOE _ St. Joe Corp., the Jacksonville-based former paper
giant turned real estate company, has combined its real estate
service operations into a new firm, Advantis, which will be based
in Atlanta. The new firm, to be focused on the Southeast, will go
after corporations in need of new facilities, expansions, property
management, etc. Advantis is a subsidiary of St. Joe's commercial
development group which has purchased two Atlnata sites and is
shopping for more. (Salter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ This was my fourth consecutive year attending
the Amelia Island Concours d'Elegance, and I have developed a real
fondness for the event. The first year, I didn't even really know
what a concours d'elegance was until I got there. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED SUNDAY.
