particularly heavy in the field of information technology. Because
schools can't produce these grads fast enough (there are 500,000
jobs to be filled nationwide), companies have to be creative in
finding workers. Microsoft, for example, is financing the creation
of its own future workforce by training people such as pharmacists
and architects to become info technology professionals. arranging
for fotos. (Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
