hailed as a hero for rescuing the crane operator in Monday's mill
fire, but it's a title he hopeps to shed by week's end. It's part
of the job, he says, just as it was again Monday when he was sent
to another fire in the middle of the night. (Cook, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
