<P>
   SAVED-GUY _ ATLANTA _ Ivers Sims drive to Atlanta from Alabama
for what's usually an eight- to 12-hour shift in a small cabin 220
feet above another construction site. he was pulling old beams from
inside the old cotton mill in preparation for loft renovations when
he saw a small fire. He worried for his fellow construction workers
as they scrambled for hoses to put it out. But it quickly spread,
trapping him for an hour and 32 minutes. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
