<SLUG> BC-ST-JOE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    St. Joe Co. creates firm called Advantis
 &HT;    By Sallye Salter
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The St. Joe Co., a former paper producer turned real
estate corporation, has combined its real estate service operations
into a new Atlanta-based firm named Advantis.
</P>
<P>
   The 500-employee operation is headed by T. Richard Bryant,
former president of Goodman Segar GVA, which was acquired by St.
Joe last September. The new firm, which also includes Florida Real
Estate Advisors, acquired by St. Joe in January, has operations
from Washington, D.C. to Miami. The firm has 65 employees in
Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Jacksonville, Fla.-based St. Joe, a publicly held corporation
that is Florida's largest private land owner and parent of the
Arvida residential operations, has moved forcefully into commercial
real estate development. It recently purchased two office
development sites in metro Atlanta. The company is also looking for
potential office sites in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Advantis plans to build a client base of corporations that need
new or expanded facilities and property management, Bryant said.
The firm is also beefing up its institutional investment staff.
</P>
<P>
   Although Advantis is a subsidiary of St. Joe Commercial Group,
``St. Joe is not going to be a major part of our business,'' Bryant
said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
