<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ In a dangerous escalation of Balkan
fighting, Yugoslav forces briefly seize a town in Albania. In
response, the U.S. State Department says NATO ``would consider with
utmost seriousness any Serb attempt to widen the war.'' By BENNETT
ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   CRUISE-MISSILES (Washington) _ The Air Force's inventory of
cruise missiles has been so depleted by the Kosovo crisis and
military operations in Iraq that the service is about to start a
$52 million program to convert some of its remaining
nuclear-capable cruise missiles into conventional weapons. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
