<P>
   BEACH-PARTY (Galveston, Texas) _ More than 100,000 people may
swarm the Galveston beachfront this weekend to participate in what
has become one of the biggest and most costly events on the island
resort city's annual calendar. The city will spend more than
$200,000 to pay overtime to the police and hire extra officers to
control traffic and prevent gridlock during ``Beach Party
Weekend.'' By KEVIN MORAN.
</P>
<P>
   DEADBEAT (Houston) _ The first federal ``deadbeat parents'' case
in south Texas ends when a California engineer was sentenced to 18
months in prison and ordered to pay more than $173,000 in
restitution. The Deadbeat Parents Punishment Act of 1998, signed
into law by President Clinton last summer, makes it a federal crime
for a parent to fail to pay child support where the amount owed is
greater than $10,000 or has remained unpaid for a period longer
than two years. By ED ASHER.
</P>
