<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CheckFree offers Solutions
 &HT;    (EDS: Original budget line for this story has changed to story
below.)
 &HT;    By Mark Clothier
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Norcross, Ga.-based CheckFree is adding a unit that
will offer consulting services to customers looking to launch
Internet-based bill-paying and bill-presenting.
</P>
<P>
   CheckFree's EC Solutions will offer fee-based consulting
services to its billers, financial institutions and software
providers. The 10- to 15-person unit will start operating in May.
</P>
<P>
   It will report to Mark A. Johnson, CheckFree's vice chairman of
corporate development.
</P>
<P>
   The consultants will have experience or training with electronic
commerce and Internet programming.
</P>
<P>
   CheckFree is one of a handful of companies trying to make the
Internet the place where people get and pay their bills.
</P>
<P>
   CheckFree shares were up $9.25 or 18 percent, closing Tuesday at
$60.75.
</P>
<P>
   CheckFree is up 29.1 percent in the last 5 days; 160 percent for
1999.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Clothier writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
