   BOEING (Seattle) _ The FAA has told Boeing it can't deliver any
planes to customers unless it first verifies that all FAA
airworthiness directives have been incorporated into those planes.
This drastic action comes after an FAA investigation found planes
that did not include changes required by various airworthiness
directives, including one to make the rudder safer and another to
keep the wing flaps from falling off.
