<P>
   SCI-HEALTH-HEARING (Washington) _ In the official government
record, the hearing that began on Tuesday in Room 2358 of the
Rayburn House Office Building will be listed as ``public witness
testimony.'' Unofficially, it was long ago dubbed ``Mother
Theresa's waiting room,'' a moniker that could not be more apt.
Here, for three days this week and two next, the sick and afflicted
and their lobbyists are gathering in an annual telethon of sorts:
the desperate competition for research funding to cure disease.
Hundreds of ailments are represented, from the most common cancer
to the rarest genetic disorder. By Sheryl Gay Stolberg.
</P>
