NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, APRIL 14
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-NATO-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Apr. 12,
about a meeting of NATO foreign ministers on Kosovo misstated the
site of a news conference at which Secretary General Kofi Annan of
the United Nations said he was prepared to meet with President
Slobodan Milosevic of Yugoslavia if that would help resolve the
conflict. Mr. Annan spoke in Madrid, not at United Nations
headquarters in New York.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ATLANTA-POLLEN-NYT (moved on Monday, Apr. 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Apr. 12,
about high pollen counts in Atlanta misspelled the name of an
allergy drug. The drug is Zyrtec, not Zyrtac.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DOWNLOAD-MUSIC-NYT (moved on Sunday, Apr. 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 4,
about the growing practice of downloading music from the Internet
misstated the surname of the chief executive officer of MP3.com, a
Web site offering free songs for downloading. He is Michael
Robertson, not Robinson.
</P>
